## RUST PATTERNS

When writing Rust code for Brush:

1. USE modern Rust idioms from the 2021 edition
2. PREFER ownership-based resource management over manual cleanup
3. LEVERAGE the type system to encode invariants
4. IMPLEMENT the `Error` trait for custom error types
5. USE associated types in traits for improved type safety
6. APPLY Result-based error handling rather than panics
7. FAVOR immutable data structures when possible

ONE SOLUTION ONLY:
```rust
// Error handling pattern
#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]
pub enum BrushError {
    #[error("IO error: {0}")]
    Io(#[from] std::io::Error),
    
    #[error("Configuration error: {0}")]
    Config(String),
    
    #[error("GPU error: {0}")]
    Gpu(String),
    
    #[error("Unsupported operation on this platform")]
    UnsupportedPlatform,
}

// Usage pattern
pub fn process_data(path: &Path) -> Result<ProcessedData, BrushError> {
    let data = std::fs::read(path)?; // IO Error auto-converted via From trait
    
    if data.is_empty() {
        return Err(BrushError::Config("Empty data file".into()));
    }
    
    // Processing logic
    Ok(ProcessedData::new(data))
}
```

