## WASM INTEGRATION

For WebAssembly compatibility:

1. AVOID direct DOM manipulation in core code
2. USE the wasm-bindgen ecosystem for JS interop
3. MINIMIZE data copying across the WASM boundary
4. IMPLEMENT platform-specific abstractions for browser APIs
5. HANDLE browser-specific limitations explicitly

ONE SOLUTION ONLY:
```rust
// WASM-specific module with feature flag
#[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
pub mod wasm {
    use wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;
    
    #[wasm_bindgen]
    pub fn initialize() {
        // Set panic hook for better error messages
        console_error_panic_hook::set_once();
        
        // Initialize logging
        wasm_logger::init(wasm_logger::Config::default());
        
        log::info!("WASM module initialized");
    }
    
    #[wasm_bindgen]
    pub fn process_data(data: &[u8]) -> Result<JsValue, JsValue> {
        // Process data and return result to JS
        match crate::core::process_data_internal(data) {
            Ok(result) => Ok(serde_wasm_bindgen::to_value(&result)?),
            Err(e) => Err(JsValue::from_str(&e.to_string())),
        }
    }
}
```

