## LOGGING AND DIAGNOSTICS

For effective logging:

1. USE appropriate log levels (error, warn, info, debug, trace)
2. INCLUDE context in log messages
3. IMPLEMENT structured logging for machine-parseable output
4. CONFIGURE different logging backends for different platforms
5. ADD tracing points for performance-critical sections

ONE SOLUTION ONLY:
```rust
// Logging pattern
pub fn initialize_logging() {
    #[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
    {
        wasm_logger::init(wasm_logger::Config::default());
        log::info!("WASM logging initialized");
    }
    
    #[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
    {
        env_logger::init();
        log::info!("Native logging initialized");
    }
}

// Usage
pub fn process_image(image: &Image) -> Result<(), BrushError> {
    log::debug!("Processing image: {}x{}", image.width, image.height);
    
    if image.is_empty() {
        log::warn!("Empty image provided");
        return Ok(());
    }
    
    match perform_operation(image) {
        Ok(result) => {
            log::info!("Operation completed successfully: {:?}", result);
            Ok(())
        }
        Err(e) => {
            log::error!("Operation failed: {}", e);
            Err(e.into())
        }
    }
}
```

